value:
Editorial title.
First work is a plan for the performance of a version of Chaconne, HWV 435, as a "Concerto" with an instrumental bass for the first group of repeats in G major, the G minor section without bass, and a closing Ritornello for orchestra. The second work is a 16-bar melody used in Organ concerto HWV 295 no. 3, and Concerto grosso op. 6 no. 9, HWV 327 no. 3.
Single leaf, p. 2 is blank.
Holograph manuscript in ink.
Watermark: "LVG" below fleur de lis over Strasbourg bend; countermark: "IV" (Burrows C30)
